	<Title>
		Applying sunscreen? Don&apos;t be stingy
	</Title>
	<Body>
		&lt;p&gt;Most people use sunscreen too sparingly. If you&apos;re wearing swim gear, it takes about 1 ounce (28 grams) of sunscreen to cover all exposed parts of your body. That&apos;s the amount in a standard shot glass. If you&apos;re only using a dime-sized drop of sunscreen, you&apos;re not using nearly enough.&lt;/p&gt;
